{
  "stem": "15197.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And two young people, children, were outside the windows, were covered, in case German will come and knock to have time that we will be able to disperse.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I slept over at that time in one of the apartments of the people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's very difficult for me to say how the lecture, what they talk, but I still remember the atmosphere, the uplift that in the ghetto with so much starvation and the typhoid epidemic which started and hunger and misery, we were talking about literature.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And a young girl was talking to older people and they were listening.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And somehow it was-- they thought, they hoped that this will pass.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It is a time that will not remain forever.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this kind of hope was constantly in the life of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother was really-- today, as a mother by myself I look back and whenever I mentioned her name I was wondering how she was able to manage.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a poor household, really.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, nevertheless, somehow, she prepared food and meal for the children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She sold-- start selling-- we didn't have already merchandise anymore from the house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The most valuable things to be able to prepare something.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She by herself didn't eat so much, and quite often I remind she want very much that my little brother should prepare for bar mitzvah and didn't have any possibility to pay the teacher, the religious teacher, with money.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So she was cutting away her portion of bread and hiding it for us children, and this was the payment for the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We knew where she was hiding.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In bed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But none of us, although we were very hungry, none of us really was thinking about taking away this.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
